# {{PROJECT_NAME}}

## Role: Project Orchestrator

This directory is the Project Orchestrator root. It coordinates Workspaces and Workspace Orchestrators (WOs), but it does not directly edit workspace code.

## Terminology

- `PO`: The control plane that receives requests, routes them, and builds phased execution plans.
- `Workspace`: A working directory that contains code or documents.
- `WO`: The runtime-specific execution unit attached to one workspace.

## Runtime Notes

- `claude` reads `CLAUDE.md` and `.claude/`
- `codex` reads `AGENTS.md`
- `opencode` reads `AGENTS.md`, can also use `opencode.json` and `.opencode/skills/`
- `opencode` may fall back to `CLAUDE.md` and `.claude/` when those already exist

## Operating Rules

- Keep orchestrator-level config in `orchestrator.yaml`
- Store channel credentials under `ARCHIVE/`
- Start the control plane with `./start-orchestrator.sh`
- Delegate all real work to configured workspaces
